Mechel, Gazprom, Polyus Gold, Rosneft: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 
2011-08-15T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/mechel-gazprom-polyus-gold-rosneft-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 2.2 percent to 1,470.56. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index advanced 3.2 percent to 1,594.68.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  :  Russia ’s largest producer of coking
coal won its bid to have a U.S. judge dismiss a class action
lawsuit filed in 2009 over share-price declines. The stock rose
1.4 percent to 557.30 rubles.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX): A unit of the state-run gas export
monopoly received approval to provide electricity to Dutch
consumers and small businesses. The shares advanced 2.8 percent
to 169.40 rubles.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): The country’s largest gold
producer closed at the highest level since July 20 as gold
futures for December delivery declined for a second day. The
shares rose 3.4 percent to 1,696.70.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Russia’s largest oil producer rose
for the first day in nine while crude oil for September delivery
dropped 34 cents to settle at $85.38 a barrel on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange . The shares advanced 4.2 percent to 202.25
rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
